OL,6,FA post-mortem examination revealed
OL,7,FOllie had died from the delayed
OL,8,Feffects of a broken neck, believed to
OL,9,Fhave occurred up to eight days before
OL,10,Fhis death.
OL,12,FThe injury had led to the compression
OL,13,Fof the spinal cord which had caused
OL,14,Fhim to stop breathing.
OL,16,FIt was also revealed the month-old
OL,17,Fchild had a total of 40 bone
OL,18,Ffractures, including a fractured
OL,19,Fskull, collar bone, breaks to joints
OL,20,Fin both arms and legs and 23 rib
OL,21,Ffractures.
