OL,6,F"An ambulance was called and he was
OL,7,Ftaken to the Leicester Royal
OL,8,FInfirmary. However, medical staff were
OL,9,Funable to revive him and at 7.30am it
OL,10,Fwas agreed that attempts to
OL,11,Fresuscitate him should be discontinued.
OL,13,F"He was then pronounced dead. He died
OL,14,Ffrom the delayed effects of a broken
OL,15,Fneck."
OL,17,FSome of the injuries Ollie had
OL,18,Fsuffered were inflicted days before he
OL,19,Fwas taken to hospital.
