OL,6,FMr Hankin added: "Although the
OL,7,Fpathology doesn't allow us to identify
OL,8,Fthe precise mechanism with
OL,9,Fcertainty... the (medical) experts
OL,10,Fengaged in this case on all sides are
OL,11,Fagreed that the neck injury led to
OL,12,Fcompression of the spinal cord, which
OL,13,Fin turn stopped Ollie breathing.
OL,15,F"What the pathology investigation can
OL,16,Ftell us is the neck was snapped
OL,17,Fbetween four and eight days prior to
OL,18,Fhis death."
