OL,6,FDavis, now aged 29, and Driver, now
OL,7,Faged 31, both of Carlisle Street,
OL,8,FLeicester, were initially arrested by
OL,9,Fpolice on 27 October 2017 but offered
OL,10,Fno explanation for their son's
OL,11,Finjuries.
OL,13,FIt led to a complex and lengthy police
OL,14,Finvestigation, involving medical
OL,15,Fexperts examining each of the Ollie's
OL,16,Fmany injuries.
OL,18,FIt was established the fractures he
OL,19,Fsustained were non-accidental and must
OL,20,Fhave been caused by serious physical
OL,21,Fabuse.
